content:
Steve Jobs said taste is paramount to business leaders who wish to do well.
I think that&rsquo;s a bit too abstract to put into practice on a day-to-day basis.
Instead, I prefer thinking of it this way: &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s not put more garbage into the world.&rdquo;
That is, it is a virtue to be critical about one&rsquo;s own works.
When our standards are high, and we refuse to pollute the lives of others due to greed, impatience, and such vices, we automatically imbibe &ldquo;taste.&rdquo;
No esoteric or mystical skill required this way.
